52
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:45,490
So we'll start out with
our usual approach,

53
00:02:45,490 --> 00:02:49,030
and we have two directions
that we have to consider.

54
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:51,620
So in the radial direction
there is an inward component

55
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:55,890
of the normal force, like that.

56
00:02:55,890 --> 00:02:59,380
And that's opposite the
angle, so it's pointing

57
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:01,060
opposite our direction.

58
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:04,460
So we have minus n sine phi.

59
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:06,980
The gravitational force is
