76
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,610
That's equal to 0.

77
00:03:59,610 --> 00:04:03,760
So in this problem, this
is the side that we know,

78
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:09,350
and we're trying to figure
out up to the speed, v. Now,

79
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:10,910
how do we analyze this problem?

80
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:13,860
Well you can see that if
I write my two equations,

81
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:18,980
this n sine phi equals
mv squared over r.

82
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:22,680
And cosine phi equals mg.

83
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,820
We have two equations.

84
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:25,910
We have two unknowns, v and n.

85
00:04:25,910 --> 00:04:28,872
Many times people
